Package: PLCOm2012
Title: PLCOm2012 Lung Cancer Risk Model for the ModelsCloud Platform
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Ramin", "Rezaeianzadeh", email = "raminrzn@student.ubc.ca",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Martin C.", "Tammemägi", role = "ctb",
           comment = "Author of the original PLCOm2012 model"))
Description: A self-contained, dependency-free implementation of the PLCOm2012
    logistic risk model, which predicts the 6-year probability of a first lung
    cancer in ever-smokers from age, race/ethnicity, education, body-mass index,
    chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, personal cancer history, family
    history of lung cancer, and detailed smoking history (Tammemägi et al.,
    New England Journal of Medicine, 2013, <doi:10.1056/NEJMoa1211776>). The
    package exposes both the vectorised model function plcom2012() and the
    standard ModelsCloud prediction API (model_run(), get_sample_input(),
    get_default_input()) so it can be used interactively in R or deployed as a
    hosted model on the ModelsCloud platform.
